snippet.title: Dr. Syed Mohammad Hussain Tabatabai The youngest Hafiz E Quran and PHD Holder
snippet.description:
Dr. Syed Mohammad Hussain Tabatabai The youngest Hafiz E Quran and PHD Holder
Toegevoegd door Xodawn laatste februari
Dr. Syed Muhammad Hussain Tabatabai is a child genius. He was born in Iran in 1990. Both his Father Syed Muhammad Mehdi Tabatabai and His Mother Syeda Amina and elder two siblings were also hafiz e Quran and his main tutor was a blind shiekh in Qum At the age of 2 he could recite the 30th sura of Quran by heart. At the age of 5 he became Quran Hafiz. In 1997 he was awarded a doctorate degree (Phd) on five subjects of Quranic sciences from Hijaz University of Coventry (UK) He is not only a Quran Hafiz, he is the encyclopedia of the Holy Quran. He can tell precisely the sura, verse and ayat number of any ayat from the Holy Quran. He can translate the Holy Quran and explain each ayat in Persian and Arabic. He has memorized 80 Hadith of Imams and has full knowledge of Nahjul Balagha. He is now studying in Qom, specialising in Mantiq, the books he is now studying are used by Ulemas and Adults and are described to be extremely difficult. He is extremely intelligent. His father is from the descendents of Hazarat Imam Hasan A.S. and his mother is from the descendents of Hazarat Imam Hussein A.S. and both are Quran Hafiz I then asked Mohammad Hossein's father to refer to other examples of his Qur'anic conversations. He said, "When he met the former Iranian President Rafsanjani, the president had prepared a prize for him. As soon as he saw the gift he recited the verse, "And I'll send them a gift, so watch carefully what their reaction would be upon receiving it"' which was referring to when Belqays (Queen of Sheba) ruler of the land where the sun was worshipped had been advising her messengers how to behave when delivering her gift to Prophet Solomon! The president laughed a lot at this and emphasized, "Mohammad Hossein your talent is unique and research must be done During one of these sessions Ayatollah Khaz'ali told Seyyed Mohammad Hossein, "I want to give you a garment as a gift on the occasion of Eid ul-Ghadir;" he instantly replied with the Qur'anic verse, 'The garment of piety; that is the best garment" and he meant' "if you can, provide a spiritual prize for me, not a material one!" The interesting point is that he is capable of fully utilizing relevant verses or a combination of them in his arguments, which is much more important than memorizing the Qur'an itself. His father says, "Seyyed Mohammad Hossein has completed primary courses in Arabic grammar at the Theological School. At the end I asked Seyyed Mohammad Hossein Tabatabai to give us journalists a piece of advice. He replied with reciting six verses from Chapter Hojarat. "O believers! If a wrongdoer brings you a message, investigate and substantiate it, lest you might harm people on the next sundawn and regret your act."
